args: Thanks for offering to help me catch\nour dinner, Pecorine.
Ha ha! Don't worry about it.\nI have to earn my keep, after all.
And just because I eat enough for an army\ndoesn't mean others should go hungry.
Also, I'm pretty good at hunting because\nI'm used to catching my own food.
Now that's what we like to hear!
But do you really think you can hunt\nbetter than two sylvans? Our big ears\ndon't let even the smallest sound get...
Heh. That's a future chief for you.
All right, now it's my turn. Haaah!
Whoa! I can't believe you shot down\na bird in midair!
Guess I'd better step up my game...
Now THIS is what I call a haul!
That giant man-eating bear thought he got\nthe jump on me, but boy was he wrong!
And now he gets to be our dinner.\nHow crazy is that?! ☆
We finished up a lot quicker than I was\nexpecting. Thanks so much for the help!
Yeah, and I got to spend the extra time\ngathering fruit, which was SUPER great.
Holy wow, you sure like apples, huh?\nYou got a whole bushel sitting there.
Oh yeah, Sarisse and her brother, Luca,\nboth love 'em. It's part of the reason they\nget along so well.
We do not! Take that back!
Yeah, so I like apples. Big deal!\nI mean, YOUR basket is crammed full\nof plums, so what's the difference?
The difference is that plums are a\nfar superior fruit.
If the two of you like apples and plums so\nmuch, you can have mine.
But you have to let me return the favor.\nWhat's your favorite food?
Sorry! Can't decide. I love all food equally.
I'll literally eat anything. Monsters, bugs,\nmonsters with bugs on them...
Oh yeah, you guys all call monsters\n＂fiends＂ here, huh?
That is NOT the part of that sentence\nwe're worried about.
How can you eat a fiend?! They're all\nweird-looking and squishy and...gross.

Have you ever actually tried eating fiend?
The meat has a really unique flavor if you
know how to prepare it properly. It's so
nice and chewy and...
Yeah, exactly. See, you're starting to\ncome around! ...Wait, huh?
Whew! That thing came out of nowh...
Uh, Pecorine? Why are you stuffing\na fiend corpse into your bag?!
So we can cook it later, of course!\nIf you're gonna claim a life, you can't\nlet it go to waste!
Plus, now I can cook some fiendmeat\nfor all of us to share!
One delicious fiend, coming up!\nGo on and dig in, guys.
I don't eat tentacles, and I ESPECIALLY\ndon't eat tentacles that are still moving.
Yeah, this is totally still making noise.
Some ingredients are livelier than others.\nThat's just how it is!
Ahhh...delicious. The fiends in your world\nhave a spicy kick my monsters lack.
She looks like she's really enjoying it.\nDoes that mean I should...?
Well, she's made me kind of curious—\nplus, this wouldn't be the first time\nsomething tasted better than it looked.

Besides, if you really CAN eat fiends,
that's something I should know as the
next chief of my village. Heck, it could
save us from starvation one day!
If you're joking just to make me try this,\nI swear I'm gonna put a fork in your ear.
Holy snot, it doesn't taste like snot...\nIt's actually really good!
I'm glad you both ended up enjoying it.
I can't believe what I've been\nmissing out on all this time!
Oh, fiends are full of culinary potential!\nIt's just hard to bring it out.
In that case, I've made up my mind!
I want you to come to our village\nand become our head chef!
Did all that fiendmeat make you loopy?\nNot only is she not actually a sylvan,\nshe's not even from this WORLD!
Details, details! Talented people are\nalways welcome in my village, no matter\nwhere they're from.
Aww, thanks, guys. Bring it in!
Whoopsie! Sorry about that.\nI was just really happy, is all.
It's just so sweet how you'd welcome\nsomeone who's not from the same race\nor world into your village with open arms.
You've got such a big heart...\nI think I love you!
And if I can't get back to my world,\nI know where I want to live!
